  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*CONCLUSION -- SUPERSEDED by the closed-form verification two cells below (kept for the record).\n  The two fits above (two-anchor + least-squares) show that a SINGLE affine relation\n  \"coeff_j(Lambda_1) = A_j + B_j C2(mu)\" POOLED across all (S,P) does NOT hold for j=0,1. But this\n  is a POOLING ARTIFACT, not a real falsification of the Casimir connection: the correct closed form\n  (derived from tau1 = tr_aux[L1 L2] and verified exactly below) IS affine in C2(mu) with slope\n  h^2/2, but its u^1 coefficient is constant in mu while varying with S+P, and its u^0 intercept\n  varies with (S,P) too. Pooling different (S,P) under one intercept therefore hides the true\n  per-(S,P) affine-in-C2 structure. The physically-correct statement is:\n    Lambda_1(u) = 4(u-th1)(u-th2) - 2P h(u-th1) - 2S h(u-th2) + (h^2/2)(C2(mu) - C2(lam1) - C2(lam2)),\n  VERIFIED exactly over the full (S,P) sweep in the cell below (worst ~ 1e-25). So tau1's eigenvalue\n  IS literally the quadratic Casimir (plus a fixed (S,P)-dependent pseudovacuum polynomial in u).*)\n{\"pooled-single-intercept affine fit: fails for j=0,1 (a pooling artifact, NOT a real negative)\",\n \"RESOLVED below: full closed form Lambda_1(u) affine in C2(mu), slope h^2/2, verified exactly\"}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"294853\" data-output-id=\"23\" data-out-n=\"122\" data-sub-idx=\"1\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"45\" data-sub-start=\"16\" data-sub-end=\"18\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[122]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrs2x3i4-bn79xkn\" data-page-width-em=\"22\" data-latex-b64=\"\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">j=0,1 affine-in-C2-alone: FALSIFIED (both anchor and least-squares tests agree)</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">j=2 (leading): trivially constant, not a real test</span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">verified positive result: top-state (mu=lambda1+lambda2) formula from Task 3</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[122]= \\left\\{\\text{j=0,1 affine-in-C2-alone: FALSIFIED (both anchor and least-squares tests agree)},\\text{j=2 (leading): trivially constant, not a real test},\\text{verified positive result: top-state (mu=lambda1+lambda2) formula from Task 3}\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "3bbfa194-b0e1-46b3-8fbd-cc65dd56f6c6"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*User's insight (opus): the eigenvalue of tau1 = t[1,1] is literally built from the quadratic\n  Casimir. Derivation at z=1: tau1(u) = tr_aux[L1(u-th1) L2(u-th2)], with L[λ][i,j][v]=δij v - h JJ[j,i,λ]:\n    Lambda_1(u) = 4(u-th1)(u-th2) - 2P h(u-th1) - 2S h(u-th2) + (h^2/2)(C2(mu) - C2(lam1) - C2(lam2)),\n  using tr(generators)=2S,2P for [S,S,0,0]/[P,P,0,0] and the split-Casimir identity\n    Sum_ab E1[a,b]E2[b,a] = (C2tot - C2(lam1) - C2(lam2))/2.\n  This IS affine in C2(mu) (slope h^2/2). The earlier \"falsification\" was a pooled-fit artifact:\n  the u^1 coeff is constant in mu but varies with S+P, so pooling all (S,P) under one intercept hid\n  the true per-(S,P) affine-in-C2 structure. Here we test the FULL closed form directly, per state.*)\nClearAll[Csite, Lam1pred];\nCsite[λ_] := Csite[λ] = Module[{m = Sum[Ee[λ][a, b] . Ee[λ][b, a], {a, 4}, {b, 4}]},\n   If[m =!= m[[1, 1]] IdentityMatrix[Length[m]], Print[\"Csite not scalar for \", λ]; Abort[]];\n   m[[1, 1]]];\nLam1pred[S_, P_, C2mu_][u_] := 4 (u - θ1) (u - θ2) - 2 P h (u - θ1) - 2 S h (u - θ2) + (h^2/2) (C2mu - Csite[{S, S, 0, 0}] - Csite[{P, P, 0, 0}]);\nModule[{sweep = {{1, 1}, {2, 1}, {1, 2}, {2, 2}}, worst},\n  worst = Max@Table[\n    Module[{S = SP[[1]], P = SP[[2]], λ1, λ2, es},\n      λ1 = {S, S, 0, 0}; λ2 = {P, P, 0, 0};\n      es = TauEigensystemCasimir[λ1, λ2];\n      Max@KeyValueMap[Function[{key, rec},\n         Max@Table[Abs[N[LambdaU[λ1, λ2][key[[1]], key[[2]], key[[3]], key[[4]], key[[5]]][1][u0]\n                        - Lam1pred[S, P, rec[\"C2\"]][u0], 30]], {u0, {2/3, 9/5, 4, 23/7}}]], es]],\n    {SP, sweep}];\n  If[worst > 10^-8, Print[\"CLOSED FORM FAILS: \", worst]; Abort[]];\n  {\"tau1 = quadratic-Casimir closed form VERIFIED over full sweep, worst\" -> worst}]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"294853\" data-output-id=\"25\" data-out-n=\"127\" data-sub-idx=\"4\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"47\" data-sub-start=\"13\" data-sub-end=\"23\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[127]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrs3xtrr-azdzsp8\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRce1x0ZXh0e3RhdTEgPSBxdWFkcmF0aWMtQ2FzaW1pciBjbG9zZWQgZm9ybSBWRVJJRklFRCBvdmVyIGZ1bGwgc3dlZXAsIHdvcnN0fVx0byAwLlx0aW1lcyAxMF57LTI1fVxyaWdodFx9\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2141em;vertical-align:-0.35em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">{</span></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">tau1 = quadratic-Casimir closed form VERIFIED over full sweep, worst</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0.</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8641em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">25</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[127]= \\left\\{\\text{tau1 = quadratic-Casimir closed form VERIFIED over full sweep, worst}\\to 0.\\times 10^{-25}\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "d0a671f2-bce1-4bd5-a155-31bd07656da3"
    }
